AFYNERIE ® process presentation

   AFYNERIE® “all-in-one” technology is cost-effective, eco-friendly and
   worldwildly scalable. The main goal of the process is to valorize
   non-food biomass without competing with the food industry, and verging
   on a “zero waste” state.

   Two different phases can be described;
     * Biological phase, which allows “building-blocks” production via the
       use of natural and non-GMO microbial community in a “drop-in”
       approach. This first step of the process will results in the raw
       organic wastes transformation by an anaerobic fermentation process,
       whithout any needs sterilisation step or pretreatments.
     * Green chemistry will then be used to transform the
       “building-blocks”, and leads to a large panel of high-value
       molecules, interesting for chemistry, biofuels, costemic and
       pharmaceutic industries.

   The overall process will also be environnement friendly, because of the
   “return-to-earth” step of the organic fermentation residues.

